observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the  Local Chief Executive agreed to require the Municipal Treasurer to:

(a) strictly collect the applicable stall fees and surcharges if any, from the              legitimate stall holders or lessees;

(b) enforce the provision of the market code and fully collect the market entrance fees for market products as required;

(c) strictly impose the regulation on the licensing and timely calibration of instrument of weight and measures;

(d) enter into/renew the contract of every stall/space occupants in the frequency prescribed by the Code; 

(e) regularly conduct ocular inspection of the market to determine compliance with the Code and impose applicable penalty/charges on violators.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to:

 (a) invest on its personnel in the Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction Office by providing them at least the necessary seminar/training as required in the manual; 

(b) prioritize the procurement of disaster related equipment; 

(c) allocate budget for the upgrading and maintenance of the existing evacuation centers; and 

(d) make sure that future construction of evacuation center are in compliance with pertinent regulations.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the focal person on Solid Waste management to

a). Determine applicable measures on how to increase the rate of waste diversion given the challenges on the marketability of the finished/processed products;

b)  with appropriate consideration of availability of funds, procure equipment that could be used in waste diversion and processing;

c) maximize the utilization of available Solid Waste Equipment.

3.27	We recommended and the the Local Chief Executive agreed to require the Municipal Treasurer to:
(a) strictly collect the applicable stall fees and surcharges if any, from the              legitimate stall holders or lessees;
(b) enforce the provision of the market code and fully collect the market entrance fees for market products as required;
(c) strictly impose the regulation on the licensing and timely calibration of instrument of weight and measures;
(d) enter into/renew the contract of every stall/space occupants in the frequency prescribed by the Code;
(e) regularly conduct ocular inspection of the market to determine compliance with the Code and impose applicable penalty/charges on violators.
3.28	We also advised the Local Chief Executive agreed to cause the proper maintenance of hygiene and sanitation in the public market.

We recommended and  management agreed that the Municipal Mayor together with the Municipal Environment and Natural Resources officer:

(a) comply with the recommendation of MGB-DENR RIII with regards to the  proposed landfill;



(b) provide adequate and appropriate garbage bins;

(c) encourage partnership with ambulant junk buyer and junk shop operator in the collection and segregation of residual wastes;


(d) exhort the cooperation and participation of the general public in environmental protection; and

(e) provides appropriate fund for solid waste management  for use in SWM Projects, Programs and Activities.

We commend to the Local Chief Executive to make a conscious effort to provide accurate and reliable financial reports by instructing:

(a) the Municipal Treasurer (GSO) and the Accounting Unit to      prepare and maintain property records such as subsidiary records or ledgers and property cards and both offices should conduct periodic reconciliation of these records; 

(b) the Inventory Committee to prepare a comprehensive inventory count and prepare a complete report for submission to the COA Office;

© the Municipal Treasurer (GSO) to observe sound physical and financial control over properties of the Municipality. It should ensure that all motor vehicles should be duly registered in the name of the Municipality and all those fit for use should be properly registered; and

(d) the Accounting Unit to observe properly the depreciation policy on depreciable assets.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive(a)	comply strictly with the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 on the granting, utilization, and liquidation of cash advances;
(b)	require the accountable officers to liquidate the overdue cash advances. Invoke the provisions of law authorizing the withholding of salary of personnel who unjustifiably fails to settle his cash advances within the prescribed period; and
(c)	file appropriate legal action, if warranted to those who have failed to liquidate the overdue cash advances after exhausting appropriate means including those who are no longer in the government service.

